<p>As a Principal, Ted serves as the primary point of client contact during our engagements.  
His responsibilities vary by project but typically include project management and architectural 
leadership roles.  Ted has the ability to understand our client's business goals, create a list 
of project requirements, then translate these requirements into the language of developers.</p>
<p>Ted is a software industry veteran with extensive engineering and leadership experience in technology organizations. He has a track record of delivering scalable, distributed systems, embedded software products, and consumer applications. His areas of expertise include systems architecture, design & development, engineering project management, and customer relationships.</p>
<p>Prior to joining Nevo, Ted worked at a startup developing Web 2.0 technologies to better find, organize, and exchange knowledge securely within on-line communities. Ted’s experience encompasses a wide range of technologies, including consumer electronics, video conferencing, parallel computing, and scientific & medical decision support systems.</p>
Ted holds a bachelor’s degree in Chemistry and a doctorate in Computer Science from Harvard University.

